# AWS resource naming

**What this file is:** The **only** naming rule file for AWS and Terraform in this repo ‚Äî one line per resource, format + example, no tag rules.

**When to use it:** Any new or changed AWS physical name, `Name` tag value, or Terraform HCL identifier under **`infra/`**.

**How to use it:** Read **Format** and **Build** below; apply every line in **Rules**; read **`PRJ_*`**, **`DEP_*`**, and network patterns from **`.cursor/rules/constants.mdc`** only; apply tags per **`.cursor/rules/infras/resource-taging.mdc`** (not here).

---

## Format

| Token | Constant ID (`constants.mdc`) | Example |
|-------|-------------------------------|---------|
| Product slug (kebab) | `PRJ_SLUG` | `ray-test` |
| Product package (snake) | `PRJ_PACKAGE` | `ray_test` |
| Environment | `DEP_ENVIRONMENT` | `dev` |
| Index | `DEP_INDEX` | `0001` |
| Instance | `DEP_INSTANCE` | `a1b2c3` |
| Deployment key | `DEP_KEY` | `dev-0001-a1b2c3` |
| Account suffix | `AWS_ACCOUNT_ID` | `017868795096` |

**Tier P (platform)** ‚Äî singleton cluster/VPC/network per product: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{role}[-{n}]` ‚Äî no `DEP_KEY` (see `constants.mdc` ¬ß Group 4 ‚Äî Network).

**Tier D (deployment-scoped)** ‚Äî data plane, images, most IAM/SNS/logs: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{purpose}[-{AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}]`.

**Tier H (HCL only)** ‚Äî Terraform blocks: `lower_snake_case`; never embed AWS type in the label (`app_logs` not `s3_bucket_app_logs`).

**Hyphens:** single `-` only; after `lower(replace(..., "_", "-"))` and every join, collapse `--` ‚Üí `-` (three `replace` passes minimum).

**Tagging:** every tag map ‚Äî **`.cursor/rules/infras/resource-taging.mdc`**; this file names resources only.

---

## Build (mandatory)

1. Load segments from **`local.solution`** / **`terraform.tfvars`** ‚Äî never hard-code `PRJ_*` or `DEP_*` (values live in **`constants.mdc`** + tfvars).
2. Choose tier: platform (**P**) vs deployment-scoped (**D**) per rule line below.
3. Join segments with `-`; run kebab transform on snake inputs (`ray_test` ‚Üí `ray-test`).
4. Collapse any `--`; validate with root `check "naming_no_double_hyphens"` in `infra/aws/aws_tf/main.tf`.
5. Set companion tags per **`resource-taging.mdc`**; set `Name` tag only where the rule line says so.

---

## Rules

### Meta (all resources)

1. **Constants source** ‚Äî Applies to: all names ‚Äî never duplicate `PRJ_SLUG`, `PRJ_PACKAGE`, `DEP_ENVIRONMENT`, `DEP_INDEX`, `DEP_INSTANCE`, `DEP_KEY`, or `AWS_ACCOUNT_ID`; link **`constants.mdc`** only.
2. **Solution object** ‚Äî Applies to: all modules ‚Äî physical names derive from `var.solution` / `local.solution` (`terrafrom.mdc` ¬ß1.4); no parallel top-level name variables.
3. **Single hyphens** ‚Äî Applies to: all physical names ‚Äî `--` forbidden in any segment or join; BAD `dev--0001--a1b2c3`, GOOD `dev-0001-a1b2c3` (`DEP_KEY`).
4. **Purpose slug** ‚Äî Applies to: Tier D resources ‚Äî `{purpose}` is kebab-case, service-prefixed when shared (e.g. `iam-users`, `docstore-attachments`); one purpose per primitive.
5. **HCL resource label** ‚Äî Applies to: Terraform `resource`/`data`/`module` labels ‚Äî Format: `{domain}_{role}` snake_case ‚Äî Example: `module "ddb_iam"`, `resource "aws_s3_bucket" "app_logs"`.
6. **HCL boolean** ‚Äî Applies to: Terraform variables ‚Äî positive `*_enabled` only ‚Äî Example: `encryption_enabled` not `disable_encryption`.
7. **Overrides** ‚Äî Applies to: S3/OpenSearch exceptions ‚Äî document in module + root `main.tf`; validate bucket override pattern ‚Äî Example: `exlservice-arb-general`.

### Networking (Tier P ‚Äî `constants.mdc` network topology)

8. **VPC** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_vpc` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-platform` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-platform` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_VPC_NAME`.
9. **Internet gateway** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_internet_gateway` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-igw` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-igw` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_IGW_NAME`.
10. **Subnet ALB public** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_subnet` (ALB tier) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-alb-public-{n}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-alb-public-1` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_SUBNET_ALB_PUBLIC`.
11. **Subnet EKS private** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_subnet` (EKS tier) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-eks-private-{n}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-eks-private-2` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_SUBNET_EKS_PRIVATE`.
12. **Subnet bastion** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_subnet` (bastion tier) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-bastion-{n}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-bastion-1` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_SUBNET_BASTION`.
13. **NAT gateway** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_nat_gateway` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-nat-{n}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-nat-1` ‚Äî Note: NAT in `NET_SUBNET_ALB_PUBLIC`.
14. **NAT EIP** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_eip` (NAT) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-nat-eip-{n}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-nat-eip-1`.
15. **Route table public** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_route_table` (ALB) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-alb-public-rt` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-alb-public-rt`.
16. **Route table private** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_route_table` (private) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-private-rt-{n}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-private-rt-1`.
17. **Security group ALB** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_security_group` (ALB) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-alb` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-alb` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_SG_ALB`.
18. **Security group EKS cluster** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_security_group` (control plane) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-eks-cluster` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-eks-cluster` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_SG_EKS_CLUSTER`.
19. **Security group EKS workloads** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_security_group` (pods/nodes) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-eks-workloads` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-eks-workloads` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_SG_EKS_WORKLOADS`.
20. **Security group bastion** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_security_group` (bastion) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-bastion` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-bastion` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_SG_BASTION`.
21. **Security group VPC endpoints** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_security_group` (interface endpoints) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-vpc-endpoints` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-vpc-endpoints` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_SG_VPC_ENDPOINTS`.
22. **Security group FSx Lustre** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_security_group` (Lustre clients) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-shared-lustre-sg` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-shared-lustre-sg` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_SG_FSX_LUSTRE`.
23. **VPC endpoint S3 gateway** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_vpc_endpoint` (S3) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-s3-gateway` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-s3-gateway`.
24. **VPC endpoint interface** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_vpc_endpoint` (interface) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-vpce-{service}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-vpce-ecr-api`.
25. **Application Load Balancer** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_lb` (internet-facing) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{tier}-{purpose}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-public-frontend` ‚Äî Tags: `resource-taging.mdc` rules 66‚Äì68.
26. **ALB target group** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_lb_target_group` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{tier}-{purpose}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-public-manager-web`.
27. **EKS subnet tag cluster** ‚Äî Applies to: subnet tags ‚Äî Format: key `kubernetes.io/cluster/{NET_EKS_CLUSTER_NAME}` value `shared` ‚Äî Example: `kubernetes.io/cluster/ray-test=shared`.

### Compute and containers (Tier P + Tier D)

28. **EKS cluster** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_eks_cluster` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test` ‚Äî Constant: `NET_EKS_CLUSTER_NAME` (Tier P).
29. **Kubernetes namespace** ‚Äî Applies to: `namespace` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test` ‚Äî Align with `local.k8s_namespace`.
30. **EKS Fargate profile** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_eks_fargate_profile` ‚Äî Format: AWS add-on/profile id kebab ‚Äî Example: `amazon-cloudwatch` (AWS-owned name).
31. **EKS managed add-on** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_eks_addon` ‚Äî Format: official AWS add-on id ‚Äî Example: `amazon-cloudwatch-observability`.
32. **EKS node group (Ray pool)** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_eks_node_group` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-ray` name_prefix ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-ray` (Tier D).
33. **ECR repository** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_ecr_repository` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{ecr_suffix}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-iam-svc` (Tier D).
34. **Shared IRSA workload role prefix** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_iam_role` (EKS workloads) ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_PACKAGE}-eks-workload-` + suffix ‚Äî Example: `ray_test-eks-workload-‚Ä¶` (name_prefix).
35. **EKS cluster IAM role prefix** ‚Äî Applies to: cluster service role ‚Äî Format: `{NET_EKS_CLUSTER_NAME}-eks-cluster-` + suffix ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-eks-cluster-‚Ä¶`.
36. **EKS Fargate execution role** ‚Äî Applies to: Fargate pod execution ‚Äî Format: `{NET_EKS_CLUSTER_NAME}-eks-fargate-exec` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-eks-fargate-exec`.
37. **ALB controller IAM prefix** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_iam_role` (ALB controller) ‚Äî Format: substr(`{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}`,0,26)-alb- ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-alb-‚Ä¶`.
38. **KubeRay / Helm release** ‚Äî Applies to: Helm release name ‚Äî Format: workload chart name kebab ‚Äî Example: per chart under `infra/aws/deployed/‚Ä¶/helm/`.
39. **K8s Service DNS (in-cluster)** ‚Äî Applies to: gRPC/HTTP host env ‚Äî Format: `{service}.{PRJ_SLUG}.svc.cluster.local` ‚Äî Example: `iam.ray-test.svc.cluster.local`.
40. **Lambda (future)** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_lambda_function` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{purpose}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-webhook-dispatcher` ‚Äî Max 64 chars.

### Storage and databases (Tier D)

41. **DynamoDB table (default)** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_dynamodb_table` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{purpose}-{AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-iam-users-017868795096`.
42. **DynamoDB GSI name** ‚Äî Applies to: `global_secondary_index` ‚Äî Format: `{access-pattern}` kebab ‚Äî Example: `user-logins` (not table name).
43. **DynamoDB docstore group tables** ‚Äî Applies to: dynamic group tables ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-docstore-grp-{id}` ‚Äî Example: ARN wildcard `‚Ä¶-docstore-grp-*`.
44. **S3 bucket (default)** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_s3_bucket` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{purpose}-{AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-app-data-017868795096` ‚Äî Length 3‚Äì63.
45. **S3 bucket override** ‚Äî Applies to: legacy/org buckets ‚Äî Format: validated `bucket_name_override` literal ‚Äî Example: `exlservice-arb-general`.
46. **S3 docstore attachments** ‚Äî Applies to: document-storage attachments ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-docstore-attachments-{AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-docstore-attachments-017868795096`.
47. **FSx for Lustre file system** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_fsx_lustre_file_system` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{purpose}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-shared-lustre` (Tier P name; single-AZ in first `NET_SUBNET_EKS_PRIVATE`).
48. **OpenSearch Serverless collection** ‚Äî Applies to: collection ‚Äî Format: substr(`{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{short-purpose}-{AWS_ACCOUNT_ID}`,0,32) ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-doc-vec`.
49. **OpenSearch Serverless policy** ‚Äî Applies to: security/network/data policies ‚Äî Format: substr(`{collection}-{kind}`,0,32) ‚Äî Example: `{collection}-enc`.
50. **EBS volume (future)** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_ebs_volume` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{purpose}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-ray-worker`.

### Identity and access (Tier D + fixed contracts)

51. **IAM service role (fixed)** ‚Äî Applies to: service-scoped roles ‚Äî Format: `arb-{service-or-capability}` ‚Äî Example: `arb-document-storage-svc` (immutable after deploy).
52. **IAM admin role** ‚Äî Applies to: break-glass ‚Äî Format: `arb-admin-role` ‚Äî Example: `arb-admin-role`.
53. **IAM deployment-scoped role** ‚Äî Applies to: Bedrock/service roles with deployment ‚Äî Format: `arb-{DEP_KEY}-{service}` kebab ‚Äî Example: `arb-dev-0001-a1b2c3-general-ai-agent-bedrock`.
54. **IAM customer policy** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_iam_policy` ‚Äî Format: `{role_name}-{capability}` ‚Äî Example: `arb-general-ai-agent-bedrock-bedrock-invoke`.
55. **IRSA Kubernetes service account** ‚Äî Applies to: `service_account` name ‚Äî Format: `{service-short}` kebab ‚Äî Example: `document-storage` (must match trust `sub`).
56. **Secrets Manager secret path** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_secretsmanager_secret` ‚Äî Format: `{DEP_ENVIRONMENT}/{PRJ_SLUG}/{domain}` ‚Äî Example: `dev/ray-test/db-credentials`.
57. **SSM parameter path (future)** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_ssm_parameter` ‚Äî Format: `/{PRJ_SLUG}/{purpose}` ‚Äî Example: `/ray-test/eks/cluster-name`.

### Observability and messaging (Tier D)

58. **CloudWatch log group (application)** ‚Äî Applies to: OTel/app logs ‚Äî Format: `/arb/{PRJ_PACKAGE}/{DEP_KEY}/services/{service_key}` ‚Äî Example: `/arb/ray_test/dev-0001-a1b2c3/services/iam_svc`.
59. **CloudWatch log group (EKS control plane)** ‚Äî Applies to: cluster logs ‚Äî Format: `/aws/eks/{NET_EKS_CLUSTER_NAME}/cluster` ‚Äî Example: `/aws/eks/ray-test/cluster`.
60. **CloudWatch log group (Container Insights)** ‚Äî Applies to: EKS insights ‚Äî Format: `/aws/containerinsights/{NET_EKS_CLUSTER_NAME}/{stream}` ‚Äî Example: `/aws/containerinsights/ray-test/application`.
61. **SNS topic** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_sns_topic` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{purpose}` kebab ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-notifications-email`.
62. **SQS queue (future)** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_sqs_queue` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{purpose}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-notification-dlq`.
63. **EventBridge rule (future)** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_cloudwatch_event_rule` ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-{purpose}` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-s3-object-created`.

### Security and encryption (Tier D)

64. **KMS alias (future)** ‚Äî Applies to: `aws_kms_alias` ‚Äî Format: `alias/{PRJ_SLUG}/{purpose}` ‚Äî Example: `alias/ray-test/ddb-app-data`.
65. **Terraform state bucket** ‚Äî Applies to: S3 backend ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-terraform-state` ‚Äî Example: `arb-ai-assistant-terraform-state` (legacy literal in `backend.tf`; migrate with care).

### CSI and mount helpers (Tier D)

66. **FSx CSI IAM prefix** ‚Äî Applies to: IRSA for FSx CSI ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-fsx-csi` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-fsx-csi`.
67. **S3 shared mount CSI prefix** ‚Äî Applies to: Mountpoint CSI ‚Äî Format: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}-s3-csi` ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-s3-csi`.
68. **Kubernetes PVC (shared Lustre)** ‚Äî Applies to: `persistent_volume_claim` ‚Äî Format: fixed volume name `shared-lustre` ‚Äî Example: `shared-lustre` (namespace `{PRJ_SLUG}`).

### Purpose catalog (Tier D `{purpose}` tokens ‚Äî mandatory when owning service matches)

69. **app-data** ‚Äî Applies to: platform DynamoDB ‚Äî Example table: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-app-data-017868795096`.
70. **iam-users** ‚Äî Applies to: `iam.svc` users table ‚Äî Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-iam-users-017868795096`.
